.ident	"@(#)niccfg:help/mem_addr	1.1"
.related /dev/null
.title Memory Address Selection Help Screen
 You must now select the Memory Address (RAM) at which your 
 network card is configured.  The value shown is a default 
 only and is not necessarily correct.  To display the list 
 of choices, press <F2>. 

 If you are unsure of this value, you should shut down your 
 system now and follow the manufacturer's instructions on how 
 to configure your card. 

 EXITING HELP 
 Press <Esc> to return to the Network Interface Card 
 Configuration Screen. 
